theorem
Th41: (p is  first-line-of-circulant implies ( a * p ) is  first-line-of-circulant)
proof
set n = ( len p );
A1: ( len ( a * p ) ) = ( len p ) by MATRIXR1:16;
assume p is  first-line-of-circulant;
then consider M1 being (Matrix of n,K) such that A2: M1 is_line_circulant_about p by CKB8:def 1;
A3: ( Indices ( a * M1 ) ) = [: ( Seg n ),( Seg n ) :] by MATRIX_1:24;
A4: ( dom p ) = ( Seg n ) by FINSEQ_1:def 3;
A5: ( dom ( a * p ) ) = ( Seg ( len ( a * p ) ) ) by FINSEQ_1:def 3;
A6: (for i,j being Nat holds ([ i,j ] in ( Indices ( a * M1 ) ) implies ( ( a * M1 ) * (i,j) ) = ( ( a * p ) . ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len ( a * p ) ) ) + 1 ) )))
proof
let i being Nat,j being Nat;
assume A7: [ i,j ] in ( Indices ( a * M1 ) );
then A8: ( ( ( j - i ) mod n ) + 1 ) in ( Seg n ) by A3,CKB3:1;
then A9: ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) in ( dom ( a * p ) ) by A5,MATRIXR1:16;
A10: [ i,j ] in ( Indices M1 ) by A3,A7,MATRIX_1:24;
then ( ( a * M1 ) * (i,j) ) = ( a * ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) by MATRIX_3:def 5
.= ( ( a multfield ) . ( M1 * (i,j) ) ) by FVSUM_1:49
.= ( ( a multfield ) . ( p . ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) ) by A2,A10,CKB6:def 1
.= ( ( a multfield ) . ( p /. ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) ) by A4,A8,PARTFUN1:def 6
.= ( a * ( p /. ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) ) by FVSUM_1:49
.= ( ( a * p ) /. ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) by A4,A8,POLYNOM1:def 1
.= ( ( a * p ) . ( ( ( j - i ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) by A9,PARTFUN1:def 6;
hence thesis by MATRIXR1:16;
end;
( width ( a * M1 ) ) = n by MATRIX_1:24;
then ( a * M1 ) is_line_circulant_about ( a * p ) by A1,A6,CKB6:def 1;
then consider M2 being (Matrix of ( len ( a * p ) ),K) such that A11: M2 is_line_circulant_about ( a * p ) by A1;
take M2;
thus thesis by A11;
end;
